==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Wariness
<hw>Wa"ri*ness</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The quality or
state of being wary; care to foresee and guard against evil;
cautiousness.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧An almost reptile <xex>wariness</xex>.⟦rdquo⟧
<au>G. W. Cable.</au>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>To determine what are little things in religion, great
<qex>wariness</qex> is to be used.</q> <rj><qau>Sprat.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Caution; watchfulness; circumspection; foresight;
care; vigilance; scrupulousness.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Warish</ent>⟦br⟧
